               <msContents>
                  <summary>Ptolemaios, son of Ptolemaios, a former agoranomos, acknowledges that he has received from Onesimos, son of Amerimnos, a cook, 300 drachmas which Onesimos had obtained, possibly as an advance for wages due to him. The receipt ends with the usual statement that the advancer does not bring any charge against the receiver.</summary>
